The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	Zurich: Fifa executive committee members Amos Adamu and Reynald Temarii have been suspended from all football-related activity for three years and one year, respectively, on Thursday, in relation to allegations of corruption regarding World Cup votes.    
	The pair were implicated in a Sunday Times investigation, which accused them of being willing to accept money in return for their vote in the bidding for the World Cup.         
	New Delhi: The Indian football team lost 0-5 to United Arab Emirates in their third international friendly of the month, being played as part of the 2011 Asian Cup preparations, here, on Thursday.         
	New Delhi: The poor financial health of the AIFF and the absence of official broadcasters will once again be on focus when the I-League committee meets here on Friday.         
	Sao Paulo: World Cup-winning coach Luiz Felipe Scolari was hit in the head by a small radio thrown from the stands after a Copa Sudamericana match in Brazil.       
	Calcutta: Delhis Ashok Kumar took first round lead at the Tata Open Golf tournament after firing a seven under 59 in Jamshedpur, on Thursday. Vikrant Chopra, Vijay Kumar and Rafick Ali Mollah were tied second with matching scores of five under.       
	Calcutta: The Royal Calcutta Golf Club (RCGC) may host the Avantha Masters, a European Tour event in 2012. If that happens then the city will host a European Tour event for the first time.        
	London: Leander Paes and Lukas Dlouhy have been drawn in group A while Mahesh Bhupathi and Max Mirnyi are in group B for the season-ending World Tour Finals.         
	Calcutta: Former England captain Mike Gatting feels that it will be hard for any player to make a difference individually in the Ashes. Gatting said: I think it will be about how well the team plays together.         
	Calcutta: Viswa Bharati inflicted a five-wicket defeat on defending champion Calcutta University in pool 1 league match of the Ajoy Ghosh Memorial Trophy cricket tournament for Universities in Bengal, in Shantiniketan, on Thursday.    
	Brief scores: CU 175 (Avirup Gupta 44, Uddhipan Mukherjee 55; Debayan Sarkar six for 23). Viswa Bharati 176/5 (Madhusudan Hazra 77 n.o.; Pratik Majumdar two for 26). Viswa Bharati won by 5 wkts.                                                                                                                                                        
